The paper also involves the analysis of tensor rank, which is a topic in linear algebra and information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also involves the study of structured depth reductions, which is a topic in discrete mathematics, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of geometric structures, which is a topic in computational geometry, making cs.CG (Computational Geometry) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the study of lower bounds, which is a topic in logic and foundations of mathematics, making cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) a possible sub-category.
